cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method for word spotting in documents using image and string representations. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of linear SVMs and Fisher Vector representation suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The integral image representation and efficient computation also suggest a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
